Twitter</a></li></ul></div></div></div><main><section class=jumbotron><div class=container><div class=row><div class=col><h1 class=fs-xlarge style=font-size:3.5rem>A Federated OpenID Connect Provider</h1><p class=fs-4 style=font-size:1.5rem>Integrate any identity provider into your application using <a href=https://openid.net/connect/>OpenID Connect</a>.</p><p class=fs-4 style=font-size:1.5rem>Federate across upstream identity providers with ease.</p></div><div class="col col-4 d-none d-lg-block"><img src=/img/logos/dex-glyph-color.png></div></div></div></section><section class=container-xl><div class=row><div class=col-12><h2 id=one-provider-to-rule-them-all>One provider to rule them all
<a href=#one-provider-to-rule-them-all><span class="icon hashlink"><i class="fas fa-link"></i></span></a></h2><p>Dex supports a wide range of identity providers such as LDAP, SAML, and OAuth2 and implements
<a href=https://openid.net/connect/ target=_blank>OpenID Connect (OIDC) <sup><i class="fas fa-external-link-alt"></i></sup></a>
,
allowing your application to plug in any upstream identity provider, but implement only OIDC.</p><p>Whether you&rsquo;re looking to secure your internal applications, provide seamless Single Sign-On (SSO) across your organization, or create a secure public-facing platform,
Dex can be tailored to meet your unique requirements.</p><h2 id=single-sign-on>Single-Sign On
<a href=#single-sign-on><span class="icon hashlink"><i class="fas fa-link"></i></span></a></h2><p>Avoid implementing registration and login forms when you don&rsquo;t have to.
Let users login with the identity provider of their (or your) choice and focus on your application logic instead of securing identity management.</p></div></div></section><section class=container-xl><div class=row><div class=col-12><hr><p><a href=https://cncf.io><img src=img/logos/cncf-color.png width=200></a></br></br>Dex is a Cloud Native Computing Foundation sandbox project.</p></div></div></section></main><footer class=footer><div class=container><p>&copy; 2024 Dex IdP Contributors</br>&copy; 2024 The Linux Foundation. All rights reserved. The Linux Foundation has registered trademarks and uses trademarks. For a list of trademarks of The Linux Foundation, please see our <a href=https://www.linuxfoundation.org/trademark-usage/>Trademark Usage</a> page.</p></div></footer><script src=https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.5.1.slim.min.js integrity=sha384-DfXdz2htPH0lsSSs5nCTpuj/zy4C+OGpamoFVy38MVBnE+IbbVYUew+OrCXaRkfj crossorigin=anonymous></script>
